<br>
With the recent changes you can now issue multiple commands with no delay, so my pet hold key looks like this:<br>
<br>
/pet hold<br>
/pet back off<br>
<br>
<br>
Pet stops attack, and report calming down message.<br>
<br>
Hate list wiped and pet is on hold at the<br>
<br>
/guard here <br>
<br>
location works great.<br>
<br>
Also with all the talk about pet breaking mes's are any of you sure, nothing hit said mes'd mob but the pet? That mes wasn't broken early, or it never stuck to begin with?<br>
<br>
Blame the pet is big, and remember so many cases where poor Gorner was blamed on breaking a mes, when he wasn't even up.<br>
<br>
Still amazing not one log file has shown up to show mes landing, than pet hitting said mob. I still haven't had a pet break mes yet.<br>
