<br>
There are 2 main issues with the pets breaking mezzes right now.<br>
<br>
1) If you cast mez on a mob being tanked by a pet, there is a small chance that the pet will break, and it is not limited to pet with proc or it casting spells either. This has happened to me while using my animation pet, charmed pet. And it has happened while in a group with a shaman pet. The chances of break are slim, like maybe 1 in 20 or 25. But if the break happens at a bad time it can mean death.<br>
<br>
2) If the pet is aggroed to 2 mobs, and say the 2nd mob is mezzed and the first is being tanked by the pet, after the mob is dead the pet WILL break mez on the 2nd mob 100% of the time if the pet owner did not /pet back off his pet. This seems like a bug or an oversight, but it is very real and I've experienced it on every occasion that I soloed with a charmed pet. Heck I do it on purpose often due to how I like to solo. The thing is, if this happens in a group, the mezzed mob will go after the enchanter and the pet/pet owner is to blame. This is a bigger problem then the pet sticking to a mob and much more dangerous.<br>
<br>
Simply put, the changes to pets concerning mezzed mobs helps a ton with pet issues and getting a pet off a mob that is to be mezzed. But it is not failproof. The changes that came in are not an excuse to slack on pet control, since they still need some control. The worst thing you can do is argue with the enchanter that pets don't break mezzes anymore so you don't bother to back off the pet. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4356">Turonyen - Level 60 Enchanter</a><br>
<a href="http://www.kupoflux.com"><IMG border=0 src="http://asherklist.netfirms.com/kupo.jpg"></a>


