I do as a matter of course /pet hold /pet back off  than resend pet after main assist mob by habbit, but don't ever say never argue with an enchanter when they say your pet broke a mez when you know for sure they didn't.<br>
<br>
Melee, casters, can break a mob by switching targets and not owning up to the fact, or even the enchanter themselves may cast an AOE stun instead of a single target one, and break their own mes. We all make misstakes, almost all enchanters have mes'd themselves in the past, so it is not hard to believe that they mes'd the wrong (read as same named mob), or cast the stun thus breaking their own mes, by not re-targeting, and not owning up to the fact. <br>
<br>
If only 1 add, can't the mes just break early or, are they a fixed duration? If they can break early, don't assume it was a pet if one is up. It just may have broken.<br>
<br>
If it was the pet, the odds are way way lower than ever before, and as I said before I have not seen my pet break a mes yet. Possible, sure anything maybe, but I wouldn't be looking to jump on the pet classes as the cause, as it probably wasn't.<br>
<br>
Don't forget that casting mobs also now cast AOE spells a lot more often, so other mobs can be breaking the mes as well. Something to think about, I know I was hit by the wizard AOE snare spell &quot;spectral shackles&quot; last night, never saw the message, but sure as hell saw the icon as I didn't resist it. That could be one way mes is broken that you may never notice. NPC gets a spell off, you resist, never see that you even resisted, but mes'd mob is now attacking. <br>
<br>
